W I G S  A N D  W I S H E S 
I  can’t tell you how humbling and rewarding  for me to be a part of something so selfless and beautiful. Having lost family and friends to Cancer and some survivors, my mom is 20 years in remission and I consider myself  lucky to have her still be around. Although this story isn’t about her, it’s about this beautiful young girl by the name of Serena who’s battling cancer and was crowned the Queen of the Night and serenaded by the talented @fjzulferino , thank you for allowing me to be a part of yours and your family’s journey @stellemie . To @martinocartier and @paulaabdul thank you for having be a part of this incredible charity and organization, this is something that’s dear and close to my heart and I’m forever grateful. 
Please check out Wigsandwishes.org if you wish to donate. Martino supplies wigs for people of all ages who are battling cancer and are losing their hair because of treatment.  @wigsandwishes

So, this just happened. I’m thinking of the right words, but they are meaningless. What’s meaningful is the love we show each other. Devon wanted to donate her hair to help someone else feel beautiful. We knew right where to go. We went to visit our friend Martino Cartier of Wigs & Wishes By Martino Cartier. While waiting a friend asked Devon if she was getting her hair cut. We explained that we were there to donate. The woman? She was there as a recipient of a new wig. There is nothing better than seeing the impact you are making. Do small things in big ways. It is a myth, a very large myth that if you are in a car accident and they know you’re an organ donor. For example, that they won’t go the extra mile to save your life because you checked the box on your drivers license. Let me explain to you  how this works first of all when they’re trying to save your life they’re not checking for your drivers license number one, number two before they can’t even use your organs they have to call Gift Of Life to verify that you are set up, last they have to get permission from your family or  next in line or next of kin. So go ahead, save a life check the box. ￼GiftofLife 🌹

We are thrilled to announce our emcee... 🥁
🎉 Martino Cartier 🎉
We are extremely thrilled, and blessed to have celebrity stylist, local celebrity Martino Cartier who is also Wigs & Wishes By Martino Cartier founder! 👏

About: 
In 1975, an unwed pregnant Egyptian woman, “Mariam” escaped Egypt and landed on Ellis Island and became a US citizen. Soon a child was born, first-generation Egyptian American that was placed in an orphanage.  Six months later, he was adopted by a loving American family. “You are special,” he was told as little boy. “We chose you,” said Joann his forever mom. That boy, although bullied, often depressed, faced many hardships, but knew God had a plan:  Change the world one head at a time! Over the last decade Martino Cartier has transformed over 1,000,000 lives fighting cancer around the world. In one day, Martino saved over 1,000 lives in Israel through United Hatzalah in 2022. NAACP named him Game Changer of the year 2021. Known for his Celebrity Stylist status, Icon, TV personality and top salon in the USA. Cartier’s famous quote “If You don’t know how to give, you don’t know how to live,” Is quoted by many worldwide. Cartier started his 501c3, grass roots, with no paid employees, TodayWIGSandWISHES.org gives women the courage to fight cancer and feel good about themselves with high-end hair replacement, absolutely free. Today will be nothing short of absolute pure joy!! Just about 50 kids affected by cancer along with their families will take over 122 Salina Rd. Today these families hopefully will forget what they’re going through if only for a minute. At 12 o’clock noon with the help of about 75 volunteers over 200 people will spend the day living, laughing, a day, they will never forget. Today they will be a full-size, hot air, balloon, magicians, stiltwalkers, face painter, bubble maker, pool party, superheroes. For the dads, there will be a blackjack dealer inside where they can play for fun. For the moms there’s a four course volleyball tournament so they can bond. For the siblings there’s a couple 50 foot slides and a bunch more games. For the children with cancer￼ inside the home there will be arts and crafts birthday parties for some of the kids and so much more. Not to mention all the animals will be out and about so they can enjoy some fun furry moments. ￼ and everybody is going to have a spectacular lunch that was 100% donated from Liceos bakery I could go on and on but I got a lot of work to do so stay tuned and I will keep you posted.💯❤️

So today on this snowy day, debating if we should close or not thank God we decided to stay open. I met this beautiful little girl named Audrey, she is nine years old and she is fighting brain cancer. Very soon we are about to place an order that’s going to cost the charity nearly $50,000 but it’s going to allow nearly 400 women and children to walk around looking cancer free for free. Retail value of this order is well over $400,000. I am looking FOR YOUR HELP so that we can continue this mission. I ask you to please spread the word, have a fundraiser at your place of work, within your circle of friends, and let’s get this mission going! ￼LETS REACH THIS GOAL OF 50k
